Schedule: a loading dose of 0.15 mg/kg of morphine sulfate was followed by CIV of morphine at an initial rate of 40 pg/kg/hr. When necessary, doses were increased every 8 hours in increments of 20 pg/kg/hr to a maximum rate of 100 pg/kg/hr. When effective analgesis (see below) had been achieved/maintained for at least 24 hours, the dose rate was decreased every 8 hours by steps of 20 pg/kg/hr. When serious side effects of morphine were observed (see below), CIV morphine dose rate was decreased or stopped
Notes: Group B: patients receiving CIV morphine

Schedule: a loading dose of 8 ug/kg intravenous alfentanil was infused over 10 minutes through a peripheral venous line. A maintenace infusion of 5 ug/kg/hour was started 20 minutes after the loading dose. At 6/12 hours into the maintenance infusion, dosing adjustment was allowed to occur in increments or decrements of 2.5 ug/kg/hour with a minimum dose of 1 ug/kg/hours. After the 12-hour dosing adjustment the dose was fixed for 15 hours/subsequently discontinued.
